here is an unofficial list of nominees 
offered by prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki to fill the ministries 
in the east blocs first noncommunistled government in more than 
40 years 
the list was provided by solidarity parliamentary deputies who 
said late changes could be made before the prime ministers official 
announcement tuesday 
solidarity or independent 
deputy prime ministerfinance minister combined post leszek 
balcerowicz economist 
foreign affairs krysztof skubiszewski church adviser 
international lawyer 
education henryk samsonowicz former warsaw university rector 
building aleksander paszynski journalistbuilder 
local government jerzy regulski engineereconomist 
culture izabela cywinska theater director 
labor jacek kuron veteran opposition activist 
industry tadeusz syryjczyk private enterprise activist 
communist party 
deputy prime ministerinterior minister combined post gen 
czeslaw kiszczak incumbent 
defense gen florian siwicki incumbent 
transportation adam wieladek 
foreign trade undecided 
peasant party 
deputy prime ministeragriculture minister combined post 
czeslaw janicki agriculture professor 
health andrzej kosiniak 
environment bronislaw kaminski 
justice aleksander bentkowski peasant party parliament leader 
democratic party 
deputy prime ministerhead of office of technology combined 
post jan janowski democratic party parliament leader 
domestic trade aleksander mackiewicz 
in addition mazowiecki nominated communist politburo member 
wladyslaw baka to head the central planning office solidarity 
senator witold trzeciakowski to chair his council of economic 
advisers and solidarity activist aleksander hall to serve as his 
liaison with political parties 
the chairmanship of the committee that oversees state radio and 
television was to go to solidarity but no individual was nominated 
