25 percent increase in prevention efforts and a vast expansion of 
the federal prison system to house drug offenders 
the strategy also calls for 261 million next year in military 
and law enforcement aid to colombia peru and bolivia the three 
main cocaineproducing countries the administration plans to offer 
those countries some 2 billion more over the next five years once 
they demonstrate solid efforts to cut down on drug trafficking 
