scheduled to begin five hours of aerial spraying in a 2 million 
battle against a bug that is capable of causing up to 50 million 
damage locally to tomatoes apples pears grapes and other produce 
millions of sterile medflies will be released in 10 days in a 
further attempt to stop the spread of the pests 
in 198082 the state sprayed 1400 square miles in eight 
counties to wipe out a medfly infestation that war cost 100 
million to fight and cost california growers another 100 million in 
lost sales 
