<TEXT>
the energy department said thursday it will put 
one of the two plants producing uranium fuel for naval reactors on 
standby because less fuel is needed nowadays 
the plant being mothballed is at the savannah river site in south 
carolina where some 600 afffected employees will be absorbed into 
other projects 
the only other plant producing fuel for reactors that drive 
nuclear powered warships is operated by nuclear fuel services inc 
at erwin tenn the department said the erwin plant could supply the 
navys entire needs 
the projected demand for fuel no longer justifies the cost of 
operating two facilities the department said in a statement 
several reasons were given for reduced demand among them 
reactor core design and manufacturing are getting better 
permitting cores to last longer and reducing the need for refueling 
and reducing the amount of fuel needed for a core in the first place 
the navy has reduced its projected building plans for 
nuclearpowered warships 
