a computer chip covered with a sensitive 
membrane can indicate when nuclear detonators need replacement and 
could lead to wristwatchsized detectors for hazardous chemicals 
bombs and illicit drugs 
the chip no larger than a fingernail was developed by air force 
researchers air force and department of energy researchers will 
concentrate on joint study to develop chips to detect poison gases 
and degrading detonators 
i think what weve developed is a very sound scientific 
technique that can be used for detecting very small concentrations 
of gas said kolesar the chemicalsensitive membrane lets gas 
through to trigger an electronic signal 
such chips could be installed in nuclear warheads to detect the 
chemicals given off by the degradation of chemicals in the warheads 
he said what we really see though is that because the technology 
is generic by putting down different membranes its essentially 
limitless 
