<TEXT>
sir peter walters chairman of british petroleum 
plc plans to retire march 10 and will be succeeded by the former 
head of bp america inc the company announced thursday 
british petroleum the worlds thirdlargest oil concern in sales 
after exxon corp and royal dutch shell group said robert horton 
will replace walters as chairman horton 50 former chief executive 
