trichomoniasis disease within weeks and there appears to be no 
embryonic damages kvasnicka said 
its really amazing he said but were still measuring the 
impact on whether we can save the embryos 
researchers are scheduled next week to check on a couple of 
nevada cattle herds that have been vaccinated to determine whether 
the disease has killed any unborn calves 
a key test will come in october when we test the cattle after 
120 days of pregnancy he said but were pretty optimistic 
because the disease appears to have the biggest effect in the 30 to 
60 day period of pregnancy 
cows have a 282day gestation period 
an acutely infected herd can lose up to 40 percent of its calves 
while one that has been carrying the disease for years can lose as 
many as 10 percent of its unborn calves kvasnicka said 
if the vaccine is proven safe kvasnicka said the usda is 
planning by jan 1 to decide whether to fully license the product 
that was refined by fort dodge laboratories 
